registration.mechanism: Events are registered via EventBus.register() methods which accept an event class, optional priority, optional key, and a Consumer callback. Registration returns an EventRegistration object that can be used to unregister. There are three registration types: register (key-specific), registerGlobal (all keys), registerUnhandled (fallback when no handlers matched).

registrationMethods.name: register
registrationMethods.description: Register for specific event with default priority

registrationMethods.name: register
registrationMethods.description: Register for specific key with default priority

registrationMethods.name: registerGlobal
registrationMethods.description: Register to receive all events of type regardless of key

registrationMethods.name: registerUnhandled
registrationMethods.description: Register to receive events that had no other handlers

dispatch.mechanism: Events are dispatched via EventBus.dispatch() or dispatchFor().dispatch() methods. The dispatch method gets the appropriate registry for the event class, then calls dispatch on either the key-specific map or global dispatcher. Sync events use SyncEventBusRegistry which iterates consumers by priority. Async events use AsyncEventBusRegistry with CompletableFuture chaining.
dispatch.dispatchFlow: EventBus.dispatchFor() -> SyncEventBusRegistry.dispatchFor() -> SyncEventConsumerMap.dispatch() -> dispatchEventMap() iterates by priority calling each consumer
